com.nexmo.client

Class NexmoMember

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nexmo.client.NexmoMember
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable, java.io.Serializable

    public class NexmoMember
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, android.os.Parcelable
    Members are users that are part of a conversation.

    Use this class to retrieve information about a NexmoMember and handle state. For example, when a NexmoMember has joined a NexmoConversation, or when he or she is typing.

    A NexmoMember can be kicked out of a conversation: 

         conversation.kick(member, new NexmoIRequestListener() {
         @Override
         public void onSuccess() {
              // Update the application UI here if needed.
         }
         @Override
         public void onError(NexmoAPIError error) {
              // Update the application UI here if needed.
         }
    });
